Detailed Description

Description:
: Start a property enumerator. 
           void TEE_StartPropertyEnumerator(
               TEE_PropSetHandle enumerator,
               TEE_PropSetHandle propSet );

           For this test, we will need at least one TA.

           Pre:
           Open a session to a GPTA.

           Post:
           Close session and check that it succeeds.

Function Documentation

TestCase_GC001_TEE_PROPSET_TEE_IMPLEMENTATION ( )
Trusted Applications dependencies:
none
Focus:
Test the functionality of TEE_StartPropertyEnumerator().
Test Steps:
Call TEE_AllocatePropertyEnumerator() 1 time, verify that the result is TEE_SUCCESS Call TEE_StartPropertyEnumerator() 1 time, on property set:
  • TEE_PROPSET_TEE_IMPLEMENTATION Call TEE_FreePropertyEnumerator() to free the previously-allocated enumerator

TestCase_GC002_Start12Enumerators ( )
Trusted Applications dependencies:
none
Focus:
Test the functionality of TEE_StartPropertyEnumerator().
Test Steps:
Call TEE_AllocatePropertyEnumerator() 12 times, verify that the result is TEE_SUCCESS Call TEE_StartPropertyEnumerator() 12 times, alternating on 3 property sets:
  • TEE_PROPSET_CURRENT_TA
  • TEE_PROPSET_CURRENT_CLIENT
  • TEE_PROPSET_TEE_IMPLEMENTATION Call TEE_FreePropertyEnumerator() to free all previously-allocated enumerators
